tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and elevated creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, bilirubinuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), which may indicate renal dysfunction and possible hepatic involvement. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal and hepatic function and clinical correlation.
